.SH DESCRIPTION
ASRFacet-Rb is a Ruby 3.2+ framework for authorized attack surface reconnaissance.
It combines passive discovery, DNS and certificate enrichment, service fingerprinting,
HTTP probing, crawling, JavaScript endpoint mining, relationship-aware intelligence,
workspace tracking, reporting, and change detection.
.PP
The framework is intended only for systems you own or have explicit written permission
to test. Scope control, recon memory, guided help, and local validation surfaces are
built in.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B scan DOMAIN
Run the full reconnaissance pipeline. Aliases: s, sc.
.TP
.B passive DOMAIN
Run passive discovery only. Aliases: p, pa.
.TP
.B ports HOST
Run a focused TCP connectivity scan. Aliases: pt, po.
.TP
.B portscan TARGET
Run the scanner engine directly with explicit scan type, timing, and optional version
or OS detection.
.TP
.B dns DOMAIN
Collect DNS records only. Aliases: d, dn.
.TP
.B keys SUBCOMMAND
Manage encrypted API keys with set, get, list, and delete.
.TP
.B workspace SUBCOMMAND
Manage persisted intelligence workspaces with list, show, delete, and export.
.TP
.B graph SUBCOMMAND
Export the legacy knowledge graph as DOT, JSON, or Mermaid.
.TP
.B track TARGET
Diff the current workspace graph against the latest stored snapshot on or before a date.
.TP
.B viz TARGET
Render a workspace graph as DOT, JSON, or Mermaid.
.TP
.B subs TARGET
List stored FQDN assets from a workspace.
.TP
.B lab
Launch the local validation lab.
.TP
.B deploy
Start the web control panel and optional local lab in one go.
.TP
.B web
Launch the local web control panel. Aliases: w, ui.
.TP
.B interactive
Launch the standalone guided workflow. Aliases: i, int.
.TP
.B console
Launch the framework console. Aliases: c, con, shell.
.TP
.B about
Show a framework overview, storage paths, and safety notes. Alias: a.
.TP
.B help [topic], explain TOPIC, manual [section]
Show built-in documentation. Help aliases: h, ?. Explain aliases: x, exp.
Manual aliases: m, man. Version aliases: v, ver.
